sentence: Was it anticipation of Ben Bernanke's Friday speech?
Maybe the buying of overextended bears?
Could you even credit the DC earthquake?
It's already been referred to as the "Earthquake Bottom" by one quick-Tweeting, stock market pundit ...
There are two things that stocks had going for them coming into this week: dramatically oversold conditions and the End of the Month effect.
Seeing the sharp move higher in stocks across the board on Tuesday suggests very much that oversold conditions have helped bring buyers off the sidelines in the short term.

And the gains in some of the most popular growth stocks - many of them included in today's report - suggests that the End of the Month effect may already be playing its part in the stock market's latest advance.

The stock had closed lower for five days in a row, the last three in oversold territory, before Tuesday's big bounce.
AMZN was among the best performing stocks in the S&P 100 on Tuesday.

Other growth stocks outperforming on Tuesday include Salesforce.com Inc (CRM | PowerRating ) , which gained more than 7% to finish above its 5-day, and Lululemon Athletica Inc. (LULU | PowerRating ) .
Shares of LULU soared by more than 11% in Tuesday's trading after finishing in oversold territory for three days in a row.
Among the better performing oil stocks on Tuesday were Halliburton Co (HAL | PowerRating ) and Williams Companies Inc (WMB | PowerRating ) .
The stocks, which continue to trade below their 200-day moving averages, gained more than 7% and 6% respectively ahead of trading on Wednesday.

What's down on an up day?
Shares of Newmont Mining Corp (NEM | PowerRating ) pulled back by more than 2% as traders took profits in the wake of the stock's rally into overbought territory above the 200-day.
